_:genid1446 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#hasValue> "Z position of the point used as origin for photometric measurements and calculations in relation to the middle of the bounding box. Positive values are aligned with the gamma angle 180° (up). Negative values are aligned with the gamma angle 0° (down).  If the light centre point is at the bottom side, then this value is the negative half of the height. See also EN 13032-4:2015."@en .
