_:genid1573 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#hasValue> "Chromaticity coordinates ratio of each of a set of 3 tristimulus values to their sum according ISO 11664-1:2007. As the sum of the 3 chromaticity coordinates is equal to 1, two of them are sufficient to define a chromaticity. In the CIE standard colorimetric systems, the chromaticity coordinates are represented by the symbols x, y, z and x10, y10, z10."@en .
